0x00-shell_basics 0-current_working_dirctory -write a scriipt that
print the absolute path name of the current working directory.
1-listit- Display the content list of your current directory.
2-bring_no_home - write a script that change the working directory to
the user's home directory.  3-listfiles - display current directory
contents in along format.  4-listmorefiles - Display current directory
content, including hidden files (starting with -).
5listfilesdigitonly - Display current directory content . long format
with user and group IDs displayed numerically and hidden files
(stating with .).  6- firstdirectory - a script that creat a directory
named my_first_directory in the /tmp/ directory.  7- movethatfile -
move the file betty from /tmp to /tmp/my_first_directory.  8-
firstdelet - delet the file betty. the file betty is in
/tmp/my_first_directory 9- firstdirdeletion - delet the directory
my_first_directory that is in /tmp directory 10- back - a script that
change the working directory to the previous one.  11- lists - a
script that list all files 12- file_type - a script that print the
type of file named iamafile.  13- symbolic_link - A symbolic link to
/bin/ls maned ls.  14- copy_html - A script that copies all the html
files.
